 <text>
  <front>
   <head>On the Friendship of two young Ladies, 1730.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">HAIL, beauteous pair, whom Friendship binds</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">In softest, yet in strongest ties,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Soft as the temper of your minds,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Strong as the lustre of your eyes!</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">So Venus' doves in couples fly,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And friendly steer their equal course;</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Whose feathers Cupid's shafts supply,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And wing them with resistless force.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Thus as you move Love's tender flame,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Like that of Friendship, paler burns;</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Both our divided passion claim,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And friends and rivals prove by turns.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Then ease yourselves and bless mankind,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Friendship so curst no more pursue:</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">In wedlock's rosy bow'r you'll find</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The joys of Love and Friendship too.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
